                    <div class="container">
                        <div class="row mb-5">
                            <p>Cloud Native Frameworks are becoming increasingly popular as organizations shift towards modern application development and deployment practices. These frameworks enable organizations to build, deploy, and manage applications in a cloud-native environment. HashiCorp is a leading provider of cloud infrastructure automation software and has developed a Cloud Native Framework called HashiCorp Cloud Platform (HCP)</p><!--kg-card-begin: html--><aside class="tab pt-3 mb-3">
    <button class="tablinks" onclick="openCity(event, '1')" id="defaultOpen">What is HashiCorp Cloud Platform</button>
    <button class="tablinks" onclick="openCity(event, '2')">Why Choose HashiCorp Cloud Platform ?</button>
    <button class="tablinks" onclick="openCity(event, '3')">Conclusion</button>
</aside><!--kg-card-end: html--><!--kg-card-begin: html--><div id="1" class="tabcontent mt-4">
<h5 class="text-primary">What is HashiCorp Cloud Platform (HCP)</h5><!--kg-card-end: html--><p>HashiCorp Cloud Platform (HCP) is a fully managed platform that enables organizations to run their applications in a cloud-native environment without the need for extensive expertise or infrastructure. It provides a set of fully managed services that help organizations to deploy and manage their applications in a cloud-native environment. HCP also provides a set of infrastructure automation tools that help to automate the deployment and management of cloud resources.</p><!--kg-card-begin: html--></div>
<div id="2" class="tabcontent mt-4">
<h5 class="text-primary">Why Choose HashiCorp Cloud Platform (HCP)?</h5><!--kg-card-end: html--><p>HCP offers a wide range of services that include Terraform Cloud, Consul Service on Azure, Vault on AWS, and Nomad on Azure. These services enable organizations to deploy and manage their applications in a cloud-native environment using familiar tools and workflows. Terraform Cloud is a cloud-based service that allows organizations to automate infrastructure provisioning and management. Consul Service on Azure is a fully managed service that enables organizations to deploy and manage their applications in a distributed environment. Vault on AWS is a fully managed service that enables organizations to manage their secrets and protect sensitive data. Nomad on Azure is a fully managed service that enables organizations to deploy and manage their containerized applications.<br><br>In addition to its cloud-native framework, HashiCorp is also known for its suite of open-source tools such as Terraform, Vault, Consul, and Nomad. These tools have become essential for organizations that are looking to automate their infrastructure and build applications in a cloud-native environment. They enable organizations to manage their infrastructure as code, automate the deployment of applications, and secure their data and secrets.</p><!--kg-card-begin: html--></div>
<div id="3" class="tabcontent mt-4">
<h5 class="text-primary">Conclusion</h5><!--kg-card-end: html--><p>Overall, HashiCorp Cloud Platform (HCP) is a powerful Cloud Native Framework that provides organizations with a fully managed platform to build, deploy and manage their applications in a cloud-native environment. It is an excellent choice for organizations that are looking for a simple and efficient way to run their applications in the cloud.</p><!--kg-card-begin: html--></div><!--kg-card-end: html-->
                        </div>
                    </div>
